strike.u: Statement from the Idaho High School Activities Association

span.span: Please check each school's homepage for the latest information regarding your child's lessons and homework:

It is the vision of the Wallace School District that students will leave our district with critical and creative thinking skills, be technologically literate, able to work cooperatively with others and be lifelong learners. We serve approximately 500 students from Wallace, Silverton, Osburn, Prichard & Murray. We are proud to boast robust educational programs, including: full-day Kindergarten, certified music and PE teachers at all levels, developmental preschool, and fully-staffed libraries and counseling centers. At our high school we support numerous electives as well as face-to-face and online dual credit opportunities. Our graduation rate is 91%.
We Pull Together to Create Learning Opportunities
